718233f-b.title: Manhattan: Central Park West - 74th Street (West)
718233f-b.text:
Central Park: A set of 2 views of the Lake in a westward (No. 1) and northward (No. 2) direction. The structure appearing in the background of the former is the old Hotel San Remo on Central Park West, between West 74th and 75th Streets. Note the solitary appearance and compare same with later views.
September 18, 1897.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

718472f-a.title: Manhattan: Central Park West - 74th Street (West)
718472f-a.text:
146 Central Park West. West side, from W. 74th to 75th Streets, as viewed in a northeastward direction from a point on 72nd Street between C.P.W. and Columbus Avenue. The above location is that of the San Remo Hotel whose twin spires are prominent. To the right margin is the Dakota, the grassy lot being at the rear of same. Across the latter feature are low buildings on the north side of 73rd Street.
About 1936.
Gift of Dr. Michael Vishenarai A.R.P.S.
